&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In my view, the distinction between &lt;strong&gt;Ahamkaara&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Ego&lt;/strong&gt; is subtle yet profound, especially when viewed from a philosophical and spiritual lens. Ahamkara is &lt;strong&gt;a tool that can be refined&lt;/strong&gt;, whereas ego is &lt;strong&gt;an illusion that must be dissolved&lt;/strong&gt;. If Ahamkara leads to the realization that &lt;strong&gt;all is one&lt;/strong&gt;, it becomes a stepping stone to enlightenment. But if it binds one to the material world, it becomes just another name for ego.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
