      <pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/the-paradox-of-paths/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5288-the-paradox-of-paths.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;The Paradox of Paths&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The Paradox of Paths 
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-paradox-of-paths&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#the-paradox-of-paths&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When we’re learning or exploring,&lt;br&gt;
whether it’s a new skill, a career move,&lt;br&gt;
or simply life itself,&lt;br&gt;
we often crave certainty.&lt;br&gt;
We want a map, a list of steps, a clear destination.&lt;br&gt;
But here’s the paradox:&lt;br&gt;
sometimes, knowing too much holds us back,&lt;br&gt;
while not knowing enough pushes us forward.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
